<p>Wow. Three lines of code (although it could be written in one). If you understand lambdas, it&rsquo;s obvious what&rsquo;s going on here at a glance. You initalize <code>foo</code> with a value, and it returns a lambda that will accumulate any values passed to it.</p>

<p>Ruby makes the solution completely obvious.</p>

